One of the sons of the former South African president, Jacob Zuma, is dead.
According to News24, a spokesperson for the Presidency confirmed the news of Vusi Nhlakanipho Zuma’s death.
The younger Zuma is reported to be the youngest son of Zuma and his late wife Kate Mantsho. He died on Sunday night after a short illness.
Vukile Mathabela, who is the Media Liaison at the Presidency, told News24 that details of Vusi’s death would be released later on Monday, once a family spokesperson is appointed.
Meanwhile, condolences have been pouring in. Reverend Jesse Jackson tweeted on Sunday night that he was sending his prayers and condolences to the Zuma family.

